// NOTE: Integrated into the Fusion FSN tree for migration traceability.
// CONTENT:
// Developer Guide: Fusion Forge Architecture1. Internal StructureForge is written in Rust for speed and safety.crate::manifest: Handles TOML parsing and validation.crate::graph: Dependency resolution logic.crate::toolchains: Traits for wrapping external compilers.RustToolchain: Wraps Cargo.CppToolchain: Wraps Clang/LLVM.PythonToolchain: Wraps UV/Pip.crate::executor: The async build runner (uses Tokio).2. Building Forgegit clone [https://github.com/fusion/forge](https://github.com/fusion/forge)
// cd forge
// cargo build --release
// 3. Adding a New LanguageTo support a new language (e.g., Go), implement the Toolchain trait:impl Toolchain for GoToolchain {
//     fn name(&self) -> &str { "go" }
//     fn compile(&self, ctx: &BuildContext) -> Result<Artifact> {
//         // Invoke 'go build'
//     }
// }
// 4. TestingForge has a rigorous integration test suite that generates dummy projects in multiple languages and asserts they compile correctly.cargo test --test integration
